      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:5:2:127:3",
      "text": [
        " لَا تَسْتَأْجِرِ الْأَرْضَ بِالْحِنْطَةِ ثُمَّ تَزْرَعَهَا حِنْطَةً ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Abu Ali Al Ashary, from Muhammad Bin Abdul Jabbar, from Safwan, from Ibn Muskan, from Al Halby, ",
          "from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘Do not rent out with the wheat, then cultivate wheat’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "3. Abu Ali al-Ash’ariy has narrated from Muhammad ibn ‘Abd al-Jabbar from Safwan from ibn Muskan from al-Halabiy who has said the following: “Abu ‘Abd Allah, ‘Alayhi al-Salam, has said, ‘You must not rent land in exchange for wheat where you plant wheat.’” "
        ]
      }
    },
